==English==
===Etymology===
[[Blend]] of '''[[Michigan]]''' and '''[[Indiana]]''', so named by the winning entry of a contest to name the area held by a South Bend newspaper
[[Category:Portmanteaus|michiana]]

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Michiana'''

#{{informal}} A name for a region of northern Indiana and southwest Michigan centred on the city of [[w:South Bend|South Bend]] in Indiana.